ConsensusPolling: "…is about winning together or refusing to play the game. Because it can be a laborious process, it is most appropriate when a group of individuals must collectively solve a problem that affects them all. It seeks to avoid voting when such a vote would generate winners and losers and thus divide the community that must support the result of the collective decision." 



More information at http://consensuspolling.org/ConsensusPolling


